<p><a name="Notes" id="Notes"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Totalitarianism&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9" title="Edit section: Notes">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Notes</span></h2>
<div style="font-size:85%">
<ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-0"><b><a href="#cite_ref-0" title="">^</a></b> See, for example,
<ul>
<li>Cover of the book <i>The Dictators</i> by <a href="/wiki/Richard_Overy" title="Richard Overy">Richard Overy</a>, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/071399309X" class="internal">ISBN 071399309X</a></li>
<li>Cover of the book <i>Hitler, Stalin, and Mussolini: Totalitarianism in the Twentieth Century</i> by Bruce F. Pauley, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/088295993X" class="internal">ISBN 088295993X</a></li>
<li>Cover of a political cartoon collection <i>Hitler, Staline et compagnie</i> by <a href="/wiki/Andr%C3%A9_Girard_(1901%E2%80%931968)" title="André Girard (1901–1968)">André Girard</a>, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/2283020271" class="internal">ISBN 2283020271</a></li>
